From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: subarr-subgen <subarr@localhost>
Date: Mon, 22 Jun 2026 18:52:57 +1000
Subject: [PATCH] 0024: per-request ignore_forced on POST /batch

subarr's #317 Slice B needs a 'transcribe a full sub anyway' action on a
forced-only file. subgen skips forced-only target-language embedded subs
(they are partial coverage) unless the global IGNORE_FORCED_SUBTITLES is
on. This adds a per-REQUEST ignore_forced flag on POST /batch that
overrides that global for one job only, threaded through
transcribe_existing -> gen_subtitles_queue -> should_skip_file ->
subtitle_exists_in_language -> has_internal_subtitle_in_language. Only the
target-language existence check (step 4) is affected; the
skip_if_internal_sub_language check (step 5a) keeps using the global.

Advertised via a new /queue capability request_ignore_forced=True (and
patch_rev v4.15) so subarr only presents the action against a subgen that
honours the flag; older subgen silently drops the unknown query param.
Default ignore_forced=False -> behaviour identical to before.
---
 subgen.py | 44 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++----------
 1 file changed, 34 insertions(+), 10 deletions(-)

